'''Emiliano Martínez Toranza''' (born 17 August 1999) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|537180}}</ref>

==Club career==
Martínez started his youth football career with Charruitas and joined [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]] later. He was part of Nacional's [[2018 U-20 Copa Libertadores]] winning squad.<ref>{{cite web|title=¡Nacional campeón de América!|url=https://www.pasiontricolor.com.uy/noticias/copa-conmebol-libertadores-sub20-plantel-y-grupo/|access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref> He made his professional debut for the club on 16 September 2019 in a 4–1 league win against [[Liverpool F.C. (Montevideo)|Liverpool Montevideo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nacional vs. Liverpool - 16 September 2019|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/16/uruguay/primera-division/club-nacional-de-football/liverpool-futbol-club/3163217/|access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Debutantes de la 1a fecha del Torneo Clausura 2019|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/debutantes-de-la-1a-fecha-del-torneo-clausura-2019/|access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref> On 30 August 2021, Brazilian club [[Red Bull Bragantino]] announced the signing of Martínez on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bragantino anuncia contratação do volante uruguaio Emiliano Martínez|url=https://ge.globo.com/sp/vale-do-paraiba-regiao/futebol/times/bragantino/noticia/bragantino-anuncia-contratacao-do-volante-uruguaio-emiliano-martinez.ghtml|date=30 August 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref>

On 31 August 2022, Martínez joined [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] on a season long loan deal with a purchase option.<ref>[https://www.fcm.dk/nyheder/fc-midtjylland-henter-uruguayansk-midtbanespiller/ FC MIDTJYLLAND HENTER URUGUAYANSK MIDTBANESPILLER], fcm.dk, 31 August 2022</ref> On 16 November 2022, he signed a contract until June 2027 with the club after they exercised their option to buy him on a permanent basis.<ref>{{cite web|title=EMILIANO MARTÍNEZ SKIFTER PERMANENT TIL FC MIDTJYLLAND|url=https://www.fcm.dk/nyheder/emiliano-martinez-skifter-permanent-til-fc-midtjylland/|language=da|date=16 November 2022|access-date=4 December 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
In June 2023, Martínez received his first call-up to the [[Uruguay national football team|senior team]] for [[Exhibition game|friendly]] matches against [[Nicaragua national football team|Nicaragua]] and [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Siguen sumándose futbolistas convocados a los entrenamientos|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/siguen-sumandose-futbolistas-convocados-a-los-entrenamientos/|date=5 June 2023|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref> He made his debut on 14 June in a 4–1 win against Nicaragua.<ref>{{cite web|title=Selección: Bielsa eligió a Matías Viña como capitán en un equipo con muchos debutantes|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Seleccion-Bielsa-eligio-a-Matias-Vina-como-capitan-en-un-equipo-con-muchos-debutantes-uc856920|date=14 June 2023|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref>

In June 2024, Martínez was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Uruguay presentó los 26 convocados para la Copa América, con Luis Suárez en la lista|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Uruguay-presento-los-26-convocados-para-la-Copa-America-con-Luis-Suarez-en-la-lista-uc890665|date=8 June 2024|access-date=9 June 2024}}</ref> On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

